{"sha": "ffe4a5e114a1b62620546c20f3621b2151d4eeb7", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOmZmZTRhNWUxMTRhMWI2MjYyMDU0NmMyMGYzNjIxYjIxNTFkNGVlYjc=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Aleksey Kladov", "email": "aleksey.kladov@gmail.com", "date": "2020-08-05T11:20:36Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Aleksey Kladov", "email": "aleksey.kladov@gmail.com", "date": "2020-08-05T11:20:36Z"}, "message": "Fix relative path handling for custom rustfmt\n\n`current_dir` and relative paths to executables works differently on\nunix and windows (unix behavior does not make sense), see:\n\nhttps://github.com/oconnor663/duct.rs/blob/17e30e83a16b202551df4d70d0b2cc174cb53e5d/src/lib.rs#L295-L324\n\nThe original motivation to set cwd was to make rustfmt read the\ncorrect rustfmt.toml, but that was future proofing, rather than a bug\nfix.\n\nSo, let's just remove this and see if breaks or fixes more use-cases.\n\nIf support for per-file config is needed, we could use `--config-path`\nflag.", "tree": {"sha": "2f9c8aaecb61c6dfc80a8b533dd3e09b00bd220d", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/2f9c8aaecb61c6dfc80a8b533dd3e09b00bd220d"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/ffe4a5e114a1b62620546c20f3621b2151d4eeb7", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/ffe4a5e114a1b62620546c20f3621b2151d4eeb7", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/ffe4a5e114a1b62620546c20f3621b2151d4eeb7", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/ffe4a5e114a1b62620546c20f3621b2151d4eeb7/comments", "author": {"login": "matklad", "id": 1711539, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE3MTE1Mzk=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1711539?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/matklad", "html_url": "https://github.com/matklad", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matklad/follower